Given a sorted array arr consisting of 0s and 1s. The task is to find the index (0-based indexing) of the first 1 in the given array.



class Solution {

    public long firstIndex(int arr[]) {
        // Your code goes here
         int n=arr.length;
         for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
             if(arr[i]==1)
                return i;
         return -1;
             
         
      
          
    }
}
